values:
Main concerns around all Owl data are:

1) integrity of the data (back end issues unseen to users)
2) meaning of the data (easy to understand, access definitions) and 
3) coverage/granularity of the data (many approval steps not captured, eg DVIP terms tab vs regular special approval)

questions: 1. Do you have any specific comments about this dashboard?
values:
Whenever I've used this dashboard, I could not get the data to match with data coming from the actual contracting systems. Not sure if this is a time issue (i.e. data gets updated in the datastore days after the event in the contracting system) but the difference was too high to be explained by this.

Also it would be very useful if we could get a cut of the data that excludes all fully automated contracts. Now - if you want to get that view - you need to have a detailed knowledge of the processes and add the contracts that do get 'touched' by ACN/Google in all systems.

questions: 2. Do you have any specific comments about this dashboard?
values:
TAT - By Deal Group (Activity) report:
> haven't used this in a little while but last time I did, seems like the TAT and/or deal volumes will change for a deal group if you run a report for the same date range but weeks later... how is the date range defined? is it rerunning it for any new deals started in that date range that have closed by the time you run the report? seems like there should be a cleaner cutoff to avoid issues? 


TAT - By Sales Lead (Activity)
> Is "Sales Lead" meant to just be anyone who's initiated a new deal? If so would advocate for changing it to "Deal Initiator" or something like that since not everyone doing deals is in Sales

This page view is generally less useful for most of my deal groups as they all tend to fall into the "Outside of N-Staff" world and harder to disaggregate... deal group is more meaningful

questions: 5. Do you have any specific comments about this dashboard?
values: N/A - have not interacted with this dashboard in the past so marked "1" for all responses; however, I do like the format of the chart.  My concern here is the underlying data is somewhat meaningless.  For example, what does TAT for "Legal setup" actually tell anyone?  The data will naturally have a high variability because someone may start a deal and abandon it or go back to negotiations for a week or two before picking up the matter again.  What would be ideal is to see how long it actually took an attorney to turn around a contract from the time of first notification to contract completion EXCLUDING all non-attorney time (negotiating, SBD delays, etc).

values:
hadn't seen this before but could be really cool - right now still too macro to be useful but I would use this weekly if I could filter by deal group & date range and get a report of the underlying deals for that query (I've been manually creating a version of this at the ATAP deal group level for months b/c didn't know how to get it out of the Owl)

data question though: why is CA at Zero? That seems off.. even if < 1 day it should still show up as 0.X right?

would also be great so see definitions of the start/end point for the different Activities (Legal Setup, CIR, etc...) - know it's probably somewhere in the Owl on a Help Page or something but any thought to incorporating definitions at the bottom of every page just for avoidance of doubt and ease of use?

The high level dashboard is good, once I was trained on how to use it. It wasn't intuitive to me at first.

I am planning to use Forms for our quizzes going forward, due to various limitations in gQuiz, so I'll sync with you on if/how this would work for reporting.

questions: 17. Do you have any specific comments about this dashboard?
values:
I'd love to see this data align more closely with how we report SLAs for query. It might be worth a conversation with Sotiris to see how we can achieve that. 

Also, I'd like to see the top table create a composite of each of the metric. For example, what is the average TAT across all levels of cases? 

The graph of case volume by week is not very useful to me. I'd rather see that in tabular form / maybe broken out by month

It would be awesome to see the table at the bottom have additional filters -- maybe a way to easily identify outlier cases with extra long FR / TAT scores?

questions: 22. Do you have any specific comments about this dashboard?
values: Ahh, this is my most used dashboard.  I get all my cases data from here, if not, then from the sql report I can run.  The issue with this dashboard now is that we have deprecated all of our email aliases!  THat means we no longer need to use HK's to tag emails.  We still get emails, but they come from aMaze which uses category trees that users select, but we are not reporting on the category trees!! I have raised this issue several times, but no one seems to care.  I trust the volume numbers here, but I don't trust the HK's and issues. The issues need to be more defined than with the few HK's we have used in the past.

values:
I think simba should just have a couple unassigned reportable free text fields so that teams can come up with their own values. 

For example a product team could decide that for them Free Text 1 is a billing code and they could report on it and other teams could do their thing as well without each team trying to justify a feature request to Simba Eng. This would help a lot with migrations too.
